==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Anorthite
<hw>A*nor"thite</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'an</grk> priv. + <grk>'orqo`s</grk> straight (<grk>'orqh`</grk>
sc. <grk>gwni`a</grk> right angle); not in a right angle.]</ety> <def>A
mineral of the feldspar family, commonly occurring in small glassy
crystals, also a constituent of some igneous rocks. It is a lime
feldspar. See <er>Feldspar</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anorthoclase</ent>⟦br⟧
